DRG ARR, FLIGHT WAS VCTRD FOR NDB RUNWAY 6 APCH, AND ADZD RALEIGH-DURHAM WX 
WAS 500' OVC, VIS 3 MI WITH FOG, WND FM 140 DEG AT 12 KTS, ALTM 30.01. AFTER 
CLNC FOR APPROACH, AIRCRAFT CROSSED FINAL APPROACH FIX (FAF) AT 2100' MSL. RADAR SVC WAS 
TRMTD AND FREQ CHG WAS APPROVED. WHEN AIRCRAFT DID NOT ARR, SEARCH WAS 
INITIATED. WRECKAGE WAS FND ABT 2.5 MI SW OF RUNWAY 6, WHERE AIRCRAFT HIT TREES AND 
CRASHED. ELEV OF CRASH SITE WAS ABT 600' MSL. MDA FOR APPROACH WAS 1160' MSL 
(WITH LCL ALTM SETTING; 1260' WITH RALEIGH-DURHAM SETTING). EXAM 
REVEALED AIRCRAFT HIT TREES, WHILE ON RUNWAY HDG IN WINGS LVL ATTITUDE; 
CONFIGURED FOR LNDG. NO PREIMPACT PART FAILURE/MALFUNCTION WAS FND. 
TOX CHECK OF PIC'S BLOOD SHOWED 0.10 MG/L OF DIAZEPAM AND 0.09 MG/L OF 
NORDIAZEPAM. CHECK OF HIS URINE SHOWED METABOLITE OF MARIJUANA (11-
NOR-DELTA-9-TETRAHYDROCANNABINOL-9-CARBOXYLIC ACID) AT LVL OF 0.117 
MG/L. AFTER SURGERY FOR MALIGNANT LYMPHOMA (FEB 89), PIC WAS RESTORED 
TO FLIGHT STATUS ON 8/9/89 AND CLRD FOR PIC DUTY 1 WK LTR. HE CONTD FLYING THO 
HE RCVD MAINTENANCE CHEMOTHERAPY AND ASSOCIATES NOTED THAT HE TIRED 
EASILY. 
IMPAIRMENT OF THE PILOT-IN-COMMAND (PIC) DUE TO DRUGS/MEDICATION, 
CHEMOTHERAPY AND FATIGUE; FAILURE OF THE PIC TO ASSURE THAT THE IFR 
(INSTRUMENT) APPROACH PROCEDURE WAS FOLLOWED; AND HIS FAILURE TO MAINTAIN 
THE MINIMUM DESCENT ALTITUDE (MDA).  INADEQUATE SURVEILLANCE OF THE 
OPERATION BY COMPANY/OPERATOR/MANAGEMENT PERSONNEL WAS A RELATED 
FACTOR. 
